    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a broad, linear power band. The drivetrain consists of a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission paired with a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. To ensure structural integrity, the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced preventatively. The chassis dynamics are maintained by a refreshed suspension setup with Bilstein dampers and polyurethane bushings, minimizing deflection during high-load cornering. While the Titan Silver finish shows minor peppering from road use, the internal mechanical tolerances and compression remain within optimal specifications for a spirited driver's car.",
